HEADWORD: Gnathostegite
<hw>Gna*thos"te*gite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>gna`qos</grk> the jaw + <?/ a roof.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a pair of broad plates, developed from the outer maxillipeds
of crabs, and forming a cover for the other mouth organs.</def>⟦br⟧
